ATTRIBUTION NOTICE

In accordance with the Apache License 2.0 under which this software is 
distributed, users are encouraged to provide appropriate attribution when 
utilizing Audim in their projects or content.


CONTENT GENERATION ATTRIBUTION

When using Audim to generate video content, we encourage including attribution
in one of the following ways:

1. Keep the default watermark "made with ❤️ by audim" in generated videos
2. Inclusion of attribution text such as "Generated with Audim" or "Made with Audim" 
   in video descriptions, credits, or accompanying documentation
3. Reference to the project documentation for additional attribution examples:
   https://mratanusarkar.github.io/audim/audim/sub2pod/elements/watermark/


SOFTWARE DISTRIBUTION AND DERIVATIVE WORKS

When distributing, modifying, or creating derivative works based on Audim, 
the following attribution practices are requested:

1. Inclusion of a reference link to https://github.com/mratanusarkar/audim in 
   project documentation, README files, or repository descriptions
2. Submission of project references for inclusion in the "Made with Audim" 
   showcase through pull requests or issue submissions to the main repository


ACADEMIC AND RESEARCH USE

For academic use, research use, publications, or scholarly work utilizing Audim, 
please refer to the CITATION.cff file in the project repository for the 
appropriate citation format and bibliographic information.

